<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>have the best of it • make the best of it</xh5><p> <i>have the best of it—</i>1. have the advantage: Though the inside passengers had <u>had the best of it</u> during the night, the outside passengers had the best of it now. 2. be the winner: In terms of overall championship wins, the Dutch <u>had the best of it</u> as they took three of the four titles on offer.</p><p> <i>make the best of it—</i>accept an unfavorable situation and try to obtain the best possible results from it: It was anything but the perfect trip, but we <u>made the best of it</u> thanks to Joe.</p><p> <i>See also: do one’s worst / make the worst of it.</i></p> </entry>
